♪ Lift our banners high...

544
00:40:24,440 --> 00:40:26,408
Well, Buell?

545
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:30,441
Just... tryin' to get my wind back, sir.

546
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:34,048
Knocked me flat, sir.

547
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:38,890
Did you hear what that... woman said, sir?

548
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:40,923
I did.

549
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:43,327
- But, sir...
- "But, sir" what?

550
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:47,047
How can we let them
go through with it, sir?

551
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:51,006
March to Denver through country like this,
without escort or protection?

552
00:40:51,120 --> 00:40:53,600
What if they come upon
a bunch of Indians, sir?

553
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:56,087
I suggest we pray for the Indians.

554
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:01,203
Can the... the army refuse escort, sir?

555
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:04,331
From now on, the army will do
what I tell it to do.

556
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:06,408
<i>(cannon fire)</i>

557
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:22,603
What, uh... What do you intend to do, sir?

558
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:43,248
<i>(cannon fire)</i>

559
00:41:51,960 --> 00:41:55,885
- Good morning, Miss Gearhart.
- Good morning, Sergeant Buell.

560
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,728
Go away.

561
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:28,208
Louise, will you please go away?

562
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:30,846
This should make you feel better.
Nice hot milk.

563
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,928
<i>(Qfoans)</i>

564
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:43,482
What's going on out there?

565
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:55,246
Will you stop that infernal uproar?

566
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:16,281
You will not under any circumstances
go off with that... that woman.

567
00:43:16,400 --> 00:43:17,003
Yes, Father.

568
00:43:17,120 --> 00:43:20,283
To Denver or anyplace else.
I want that clearly understood.

569
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:22,368
Yes, Father.

570
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:25,406
Now will you please leave me alone?

571
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:35,926
(whispers) Is he better?

572
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:38,008
I'm afraid not.

573
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:41,923
Louise, go and get me some
more blankets. Lots of them.

574
00:43:42,040 --> 00:43:45,601
I want him to perspire. We will
sweat the poison out of his system.

575
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:48,405
Blankets. All right, Mrs Massingale.

576
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:58,887
- Mrs Massingale!
- Lie back.

577
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:04,002
- Madam...
- Back.

578
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:09,689
Now... just be quiet, please.
Don't exert yourself.

579
00:44:10,520 --> 00:44:13,524
- Madam, we have a surgeon.
- Just relax.

580
00:44:13,640 --> 00:44:15,608
Let the blood flow.

581
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:19,609
Now tell me, Colonel, does
the pain centre lie about here?

582
00:44:19,720 --> 00:44:21,688
Look, Mrs...

583
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:27,009
- It's a little higher.
- A little higher. Yes, of course.

584
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:37,370
- About this march, Mrs Massingale...
- Just unwind.

585
00:44:37,480 --> 00:44:40,131
This march to Denver... impossible.

586
00:44:40,360 --> 00:44:44,410
Right here, at this junction,
Colonel, a series of cords.

587
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:50,564
And beneath them, intertwined nerves
like fine silk threads.

588
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,971
Matters of... transportation.

589
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:57,762
Rattlesnakes...

590
00:44:57,880 --> 00:45:01,248
All connected up to here
where the pain centre lies.

591
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:05,888
Examine my position.

592
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:08,608
Consider, if you will...

593
00:45:10,440 --> 00:45:13,842
- Oh, that feels good.
- That's the key point.

594
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:17,409
First we rub gently downwards,

595
00:45:18,240 --> 00:45:20,607
and then upwards,

596
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:23,282
and then downwards again.

597
00:45:23,640 --> 00:45:27,645
Now you're beginning to relax.
I can feel it in my fingers.

598
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:29,728
I wish I could help you, but...

599
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:33,208
Army regulations.

600
00:45:33,960 --> 00:45:36,122
Article 12,

601
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:38,208
section 26,

602
00:45:39,120 --> 00:45:41,521
Paragraph,"...

603
00:45:41,640 --> 00:45:42,971
<i>(sighs)</i>

604
00:45:43,080 --> 00:45:45,048
That's right.

605
00:45:45,880 --> 00:45:49,441
Relax. Relax.

606
00:46:00,240 --> 00:46:02,607
Company, attention!

607
00:46:03,080 --> 00:46:05,606
Company, attention!

608
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:33,841
Good morning, Colonel Gearhart.

609
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:35,849
Good morning, Father.

610
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:37,928
Morning, ladies.

611
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:47,841
- Who are those men at the gate?
- Husbands. Not all the ladies are single.

612
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:52,249
- What do they want here?
- The ladies are takin' their wagons away.

613
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:56,443
They want the colonel
to do something about it, sir.

614
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:05,204
- Sir.
- Well?

615
00:47:05,320 --> 00:47:07,561
Does the colonel intend...

616
00:47:07,680 --> 00:47:11,321
I mean to say, sir, will the escort party...

617
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:14,762
Sir, do you really intend
to go through with this thing?

618
00:47:14,880 --> 00:47:18,043
Buell, you've got a great deal
to learn about military science.

619
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:20,322
A simple matter
of objective and stratagem.

620
00:47:20,440 --> 00:47:23,284
Objective - get rid of these damn women.

621
00:47:23,400 --> 00:47:25,448
- Stratagem...
- Take 'em to Denver, sir?

622
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:28,245
- Mount up, Buell. Mount up.
- Yes, sir.

623
00:47:33,920 --> 00:47:36,241
- Move them out, Brady.
- Yes, sir.

