675
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:30,248
A-marchin' out there
to intercept that wagon train

676
00:52:30,360 --> 00:52:32,328
and see that whiskey gets home.

677
00:52:32,440 --> 00:52:36,968
Hold on, Oracle. We're workin' men.
We're miners. We ain't lnjun fighters.

678
00:52:37,080 --> 00:52:41,290
I ain't marchin' up any rivers, sleeping
on the rocks and cookin' on campfires.

679
00:52:41,400 --> 00:52:45,371
You gonna spend the whole winter
in Denver without no whiskey?

680
00:53:01,640 --> 00:53:04,564
<i>At dawn the morning of November 17th,</i>

681
00:53:04,680 --> 00:53:08,321
<i>the second cavalry patrol
was heading due south for Denver,</i>

682
00:53:08,440 --> 00:53:11,284
<i>with of course the temperance marchers.</i>

683
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:15,443
<i>The Wallingham wagon train
was turning west.</i>

684
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:19,681
<i>The first cavalry patrol
