00:54:41,200 --> 00:54:44,602
We, the Irish Teamsters,
have a petition of grievances.

702
00:54:44,720 --> 00:54:46,882
We state in plain and simple terms

703
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:50,243
the bad conditions under which
we've been forced to labour,

704
00:54:50,360 --> 00:54:54,888
and do hereby raise formal objection
to the followin', to wit:

705
00:54:55,320 --> 00:54:58,244
travel hours and harnessin', unharnessin',

706
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:03,050
carin' for horses, loadin', unloadin',

707
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:06,207
beddin', guard duty,

708
00:55:07,240 --> 00:55:09,163
poor drinkin' water,

709
00:55:09,880 --> 00:55:13,282
order of wagons in march,
and, might I add, in addition to

710
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:16,324
no whiskey ration whatsoever

711
00:55:16,440 --> 00:55:18,807
in a whole cargo of whiskey.

712
00:55:21,360 --> 00:55:25,126
Now, suppose these grievances
of yours aren't answered?

713
00:55:26,080 --> 00:55:30,722
- What'll you do? Strike?
- That's an ugly word to a workin' man.

714
00:55:30,840 --> 00:55:33,002
- But it would be considered.
- Ah...

715
00:55:33,120 --> 00:55:36,044
Well, in that case, O'Flaherty, you strike.

716
00:55:37,760 --> 00:55:40,889
- Strike.
- And who, might I ask, pray tell me,

717
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:44,607
are you goin' to get to drive
your sweatin', rotten wagons?

718
00:55:45,240 --> 00:55:46,924
<i>(hoof beats)</i>

719
00:55:51,880 --> 00:55:54,963
- There are your grievances.
- We've struck off 12 more copies.

720
00:55:55,080 --> 00:55:57,048
Exploiter! Capitalist!

721
00:55:57,160 --> 00:55:59,322
Highbinder! Profiteer!

722
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:18,201
Mr Wallingham, I presume.
Captain Slater at your service.

723
00:56:18,320 --> 00:56:20,402
Colonel Gearhart sends his compliments.

724
00:56:20,520 --> 00:56:23,922
He's most happy to comply with
your request for escort to Denver.

725
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:26,008
Good for Colonel Gearhart.

726
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:28,726
Have you seen any Indians?
A scout informed me...

727
00:56:28,840 --> 00:56:33,448
There aren't any Indians here. Haven't
you heard of the Peace Commission?

728
00:56:33,560 --> 00:56:37,167
With a cargo like this,
you've got to be sure, damn sure!

729
00:56:37,280 --> 00:56:39,851
Indians, revenue agents,
temperance women.

730
00:56:39,960 --> 00:56:41,610
- Oh, you know.
- Know what?

731
00:56:41,720 --> 00:56:43,722
- About Cora Massingale.
- Where?

732
00:56:43,840 --> 00:56:45,808
It's all right. She's not here.

733
00:56:45,920 --> 00:56:48,730
She's at Fort Russell
giving temperance lectures.

734
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:52,561
- Are you positive she's at Fort Russell?
- I positively guarantee it.

735
00:56:52,680 --> 00:56:56,321
She isn't any nearer your cargo
than... than the Indians are.

736
00:57:02,720 --> 00:57:04,882
- Hope it's hot.
<i>- (Giggling)</i>

737
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:07,162
Wait till we get you in.

738
00:57:39,360 --> 00:57:41,328
- (cracking)
- Oh!

739
00:57:53,120 --> 00:57:55,088
Sergeant, I, uh...

740
00:58:10,000 --> 00:58:12,002
We've got a morale problem, sir.

741
00:58:12,120 --> 00:58:14,122
Take care of it, Buell.

742
00:58:14,240 --> 00:58:18,643
I think the colonel will have to
root it out, sir, right at the core.

743
00:58:18,760 --> 00:58:21,240
The ladies, sir, are taking baths...

744
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:25,241
in the nude.

745
00:58:38,360 --> 00:58:40,840
Mrs Massingale, I'd like a word with you.

746
00:58:54,720 --> 00:58:58,850
Would you mind calling some other time,
Colonel? I'm taking a bath.

747
00:58:58,960 --> 00:59:01,008
I am well aware that you're taking a bath.

748
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:05,523
I don't care how dirty you are. I will not
have you ladies bathing in the nude.

749
00:59:05,640 --> 00:59:07,642
There's no other way I know of, Colonel.

750
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:11,287
The opportunity was there and...
who knows what tomorrow might bring?

751
00:59:11,400 --> 00:59:14,324
Especially now that
we've changed our plans.

752
00:59:14,440 --> 00:59:17,410
- Changed your plans?
- Yes, Colonel.

753
00:59:19,640 --> 00:59:22,211
You mean you want to go
back to Cheyenne now?

754
00:59:22,320 --> 00:59:26,370
Don't be ridiculous. Of course not.
We want only to meet the wagon train.

755
00:59:26,480 --> 00:59:30,087
But you are meeting the train.
That's why we're going to Denver.

756
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:33,044
But we want to meet it
long before it reaches Denver.

757
00:59:33,160 --> 00:59:35,322
- That's not possible.
- On the contrary.

758
00:59:35,440 --> 00:59:39,843
We now intend to intercept
the wagon train along the River Platte.

759
00:59:40,480 --> 00:59:42,642
(shouts) You what?

760
00:59:43,960 --> 00:59:47,760
In a clash of wills, Colonel,
he who shouts loudest is lost.

761
00:59:47,880 --> 00:59:49,848
Madam...

762
00:59:49,960 --> 00:59:54,887
If I understand, you are going to lead your
ladies through unsettled Plains country

763
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:58,243
- along the South Platte River trail.
- Exactly.

764
00:59:58,360 --> 01:00:02,160
And upon meeting the wagon train, I
surmise you will put on a demonstration,

765
01:00:02,280 --> 01:00:05,329
whose purpose is to tum back the train.

766
01:00:05,440 --> 01:00:06,885
Precisely.

767
01:00:07,800 --> 01:00:11,009
Very well. But if you think
the United States Army

768
01:00:11,120 --> 01:00:14,727
is going to escort a bunch of
harebrained females across open desert,

769
01:00:14,840 --> 01:00:19,289
bent on throwing themselves under
horse teams, you're gravely mistaken.

770
01:00:19,400 --> 01:00:23,724
Very well. I thank you
for your many courtesies thus far,

771
01:00:23,840 --> 01:00:27,731
but if you force us to go our way
unescorted and any harm comes to us,

772
01:00:27,840 --> 01:00:33,244
three million infuriated women will
turn the War Department upside down.

773
01:00:35,040 --> 01:00:40,763
Mrs Massingale, if I could force you
to do anything, which obviously I cannot,

774
01:00:40,880 --> 01:00:45,044
it would be to go home, and stay home,
where all decent women belong.

775
01:01:08,480 --> 01:01:10,448
- Sergeant.
- Sir?

776
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:14,528
- Dammit.
- Yes, sir.

777
01:01:16,320 --> 01:01:19,722
Sergeant, I want some scouts
on the trail of those women tomorrow.

778
01:01:19,840 --> 01:01:22,161
Have them keep
in constant touch with us.

779
01:01:22,280 --> 01:01:24,647
We'll move in a somewhat
parallel direction.

780
01:01:24,760 --> 01:01:26,728
Yes, sir.

781
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:31,762
Excuse me, sir. Parallel direction...

782
01:01:32,600 --> 01:01:35,410
Is that a new tactic, sir?
I'm not acquainted with it.

783
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:39,206
- It was well known throughout the war.
- Yes, sir, of course.

784
01:01:40,400 --> 01:01:43,006
- What's it called, sir?
- Called?

785
01:01:43,120 --> 01:01:47,808
What command shall I give the men?
"Move in a somewhat parallel direction"?

786
01:01:47,920 --> 01:01:50,844
It's called... detached contact.

787
01:01:52,280 --> 01:01:53,486
Detached contact?

788
01:01:53,600 --> 01:01:56,410
And let it so be recorded
in the daily journal!

789
01:01:57,440 --> 01:01:59,408
Yes, sir.

790
01:02:21,480 --> 01:02:26,042
<i>No documents can establish just how
the Sioux formulated their plans,</i>

791
01:02:26,160 --> 01:02:29,323
<i>although it's known
that a plan was so formulated.</i>

792
01:02:29,440 --> 01:02:31,647
<i>All we can do is surmise what was said.</i>

793
01:02:32,360 --> 01:02:34,328
<i>(speaks Sioux)</i>

794
01:02:35,080 --> 01:02:39,165
<i>White man win war.
Now we use white man's way.</i>

795
01:02:41,160 --> 01:02:47,247
<i>You, Chief Walks-Stooped-Over, with
20 braves attack front of wagon train,</i>

796
01:02:47,360 --> 01:02:49,328
<i>and draw off guard.</i>

797
01:02:50,720 --> 01:02:54,042
<i>You, Chief Elks-Runner, with 20 braves</i>

798
01:02:54,160 --> 01:02:57,801
<i>attack rear of wagon train
and draw off guard.</i>

799
01:02:57,920 --> 01:03:01,288
<i>All other braves
attack centre of wagon train.</i>

800
01:03:01,960 --> 01:03:04,281
<i>When Long Knives chase braves,</i>

801
01:03:04,400 --> 01:03:08,325
<i>then great Chief 5 Barrels
